President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate key additions to his Administration. Marshall Billingslea of Virginia will be nominated as Assistant Secretary for Terrorist Financing at the Department of the Treasury. Billingslea has extensive experience in the federal government, including serving in the U.S. Department of Defense and as NATO Assistant Secretary General for Defense Investment. He has also worked on Capitol Hill. Gilbert B. Kaplan of Washington, D.C. will be nominated as Under Secretary of Commerce for International Trade. Kaplan is a partner at King & Spalding and has a successful track record in anti-subsidy cases against China. He is also the co-founder of the Manufacturing Policy Initiative at Indiana University. John Marshall Mitnick of Virginia will be nominated as General Counsel at the Department of Homeland Security. Mitnick currently serves as Senior Vice President, General Counsel, and Secretary at the Heritage Foundation. He has previous experience in the White House and at Raytheon Technical Services Company. John J. Sullivan of Maryland will be nominated as Deputy Secretary of State and will concurrently serve as Deputy Secretary of State for Management and Resources. Sullivan is a partner at Mayer Brown LLP and has held senior positions at the Justice, Defense, and Commerce Departments. He has also served as Deputy Secretary of Commerce.